All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
AddPartController
This Java class handles all ButtonEvents such as adding switching between InHouse and Outsourced, saving the Part, exiting to the Main Menu, and catching errors when entering data for the Part
AddProductController
This Java class handles all ButtonEvents such as adding an associatedPart, removing an associatedPart, saving the Product, exiting to the Main Menu, and catching errors when entering data for the Product
InHouse
Part that has a MachineID attached.
Inventory
This class is what stores the Parts and Products of the company.
MainApplication
This Java class launches when the program is first opened and displays the Main Menu window.
MainController
This Java class handles ButtonEvents that lead to new menus for adding, modifying, or deleting Parts and Products, along with showing the Parts and Products in TableViews and allowing the user to search through both tables, and exit the program.
ModifyPartController
This Java class handles all ButtonEvents such as adding switching between InHouse and Outsourced, updating the modified Part, exiting to the Main Menu, and catching errors when entering data for the Part
ModifyProductController
This Java class handles all ButtonEvents such as adding an associatedPart, removing an associatedPart, replacing the modified Product, exiting to the Main Menu, and catching errors when entering data for the Product
Outsourced
Part that has a CompanyName attached.
Part
 
Product
Products are composed of one or more Part.
